EASY-TO-READ TERMS OF USE
-------------------------
You are welcome to hack on this project, as long as I can decide when the first
public release is. After that it becomes normal open source software.

TERMS OF USE
------------
This software will be released under an open source software license when I deem
it suitable for a public release. Until such time, this source code is provided
for educational purposes only, though I make no guarantee that you can or should
learn anything from it. That means that you may download, examine, and compile
this software's source code. You may also modify it on your computer, but you
may not publicly release modifications or reuse the code in other software until
I have made a public release. I will be happy to make exceptions on a
case-by-case basis and provide this code to you under an open source software
license, but only with my express permission.

Specifically, I hereby grant my permission to anyone wishing to modify the
source code for the purpose of improving this software, to use the source code
under the terms of the GNU General Public License, version 3, provided that all
such modifications are submitted to me in the form of patches.

THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,
FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE
AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER
